the results for each set of results of our astrometrical simulations</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(9, 'resume', 'Education', 4, '<div class="education">\r\n<div class="recent"><p>\r\n<a href="http://www.ubishops.ca/index.html">Bishop’s University</a> <br />\r\nBSc: Honours Physics, <br />\r\nMathematics Minor <br />\r\n2006 – 2009</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="description"><p>\r\n<a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis">Physics Honours Thesis</a>: On the Nature of Dynamical Instabilities in Interacting Binary Star Systems (Cataclysmic  Variables)\r\nProgrammed astrometrical computer simulations in FORTRAN for my Thesis \r\nServed on the committee that was involved in hiring a professor for the Physics Department</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="past">\r\n<div class="pastLeft"><p>\r\n<a href="http://www.cegep-heritage.qc.ca/">Heritage College (Cégep)</a> <br />\r\nDiploma, Pure and Applied Sciences <br />\r\n2004 – 2006</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="pastRight"><p>\r\n<a href="http://www.hadleypwhs.com/hp/Welcome.html" >Philemon Wright High School </a><br />\r\nHigh School Diploma <br />\r\n2001 – 2004</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>      '),
(10, 'resume', 'Awards and Scholarships', 5, '<div class="awards">\r\n<h4>\r\nUndergraduate Student Research Award (USRA)</h4>\r\n<blockquote>Undergraduate Student Research Awards (USRA) are meant to stimulate your interest in research in the natural sciences and engineering. They are also meant to encourage you to undertake graduate studies and pursue a research career in these fields. If you would like to gain research work experience that complements your studies in an academic setting ... <a href="http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Students-Etudiants/UG-PC/USRA-BRPC_eng.asp">Full \r\nSite</a></blockquote>\r\n<h4>\r\nBishop’s Faculty Prize in Physics</h4>\r\n<blockquote>\r\nFor the U1 Physics student with the highest average in his or her Physics\r\nand Mathematics courses, based on at least 15 credits... <a href="http://www.ubishops.ca/fileadmin/bishops_documents/academic_calendar/53-Scholarship-Loans.pdf">Full \r\nPdf</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h4>\r\nInducted into the Golden Key International Honours Society</h4>\r\n<blockquote>Golden Key is one of the largest, most renowned international honour societies with 400 chapters in eight countries around the world...<a href="http://www.goldenkey.org/gk/gksite/defaultsplash.aspx">Full \r\nSite</a></blockquote>\r\n<h4>\r\nBishops University Entrance Scholarship (renewed every year) </h4><blockquote>\r\n<a href="http://www.ubishops.ca/fileadmin/bishops_documents/academic_calendar/53-Scholarship-Loans.pdf">Description</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>'),
(11, 'artwork', 'Artwork', 1, '        <div class="containerLeft">\r\n<div class="artbox">\r\n<h4>Mixed Media</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Mixed-Media1.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Mixed Media 1">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Mixed-Media1.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Mixed-Media2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Mixed Media 2">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Mixed-Media2.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Pastel-and-Ink-Portrait.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Pastel and Ink Portrait">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Pastel-and-Ink-Portrait.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Portrait-of-a-woman.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Portrait of a woman">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Portrait-of-a-woman.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Bird1.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Bird 1">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Bird1.png" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Bird2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Bird 2">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Bird2.png" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Bird3.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Bird 3">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Bird3.png" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Bird-Composition.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Bird Composition">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Bird-Composition.png" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Ink-and-White-Gauche-portrait.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Ink and White Gauche Portrait">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Ink-and-White-Gauche-portrait.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Ink-Portrait.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Ink Portrait">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Ink-Portrait.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Pavillion-Model2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Pavillion Model 1">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Pavillion-Model2.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Pavillion-Model.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Pavillion Model 2">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Pavillion-Model.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Section-of-Model.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Section of Pavillion Model">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Section-of-Model.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Abstract.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Abstract">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Abstract.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Escher-Inspired-Doorway.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Escher Inspired Doorway">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Escher-Inspired-Doorway.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/MixedMedia/Perspective.JPG" rel="shadowbox[MixedMedia]" title="Perspective">\r\n<img src="/content/MixedMedia/thumbs/thumb_Perspective.JPG" /></a>\r\n<p>\r\nArchitecture at McGill was one of the most liberating experiences of my life. It pushed the perception of what I could do to even greater limits and exposed me to a world I had never taken part in before. By Comparing the Mixed Media and Sketches galleries you can see that my comfort level with different mediums grows exponentially from the stick figures I began with to the full mixed media productions at the end.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThese pieces of art were all done in my freehand drawing class at <a href="http://www.mcgill.ca">McGill University</a>. Materials include: Pencil, Black ink, charcoal, pastels and gouache were all included somewhere within these works.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="containerRight">\r\n<div class="artbox">\r\n<h4>Sketches</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch01.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Thirty Second Sketch">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch01.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch02.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Thirty Second Sketches 2">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch02.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch03.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Fifteen Second Faces">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch03.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch04.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Cowboy">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch04.jpg" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch05.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Bald Man">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch05.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch06.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Old Woman">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch06.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch07.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Kimono">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch07.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch08.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Pondering">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch08.jpg" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch09.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Portrait of a Bald Woman">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch09.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch10.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Trouble with Eyes">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch10.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch11.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Portrait">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch11.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch12.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Playing with Short Hair">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch12.jpg" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch13.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Using Ink and Broken Popsicle Sticks">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch13.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketch14.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Hello Banjo">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketch14.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketchbook1.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="3 Headed Bird - Architecture Design Class">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketchbook1.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/sketches/sketchbook2.jpg" rel="shadowbox[Sketches]" title="Bird Sanctuary - Architecture Design Class">\r\n<img src="/content/sketches/thumbs/thumb_sketchbook2.jpg" /></a>\r\n<p>\r\nThese sketches are a clear representation of my artist ability when I started my studies at McGill University. I had to take baby steps, and slowly find my own technique and style. I like these drawings because they are raw and true to myself, they haven&#1268; been worked and reworked, some of them were even completed in 30 seconds, all of them under 5 minutes. Not enough time to think, just to react. Using such a quick paced method really gets you in the mood to draw and I know that I wouldn&#1268; of had the confidence to draw full portraits if I hadn&#1268; started small.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div> '),
(12, 'thesis', 'Physics Honours Thesis', 1, '<div class="center">\r\n<h3 >On the Nature of Dynamical Instabilities in Interacting Binary Systems</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Jacob Hooey</strong><br />\r\nJuly 28, 2009<br />\r\nBishop''s University<br />\r\n© 2009</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30%; margin-right: 30%;font-size:14px;font-style:italic;">A thesis submitted in partial \r\nfulfillment of the requirements for the degree\r\nof Bachelor of Science (Honours Physics)</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight:bold;">Department of Physics\r\nBishop''s University</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Abstract</h4>\r\n<p class="justify">In this thesis we will analyze the limits of stability in interacting binaries containing compact accretors. The specific case that will be used for this investigation is the case of <a href="http://imagine.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/science/know_l2/cataclysmic_variables.html">Cataclysmic Variables</a> (CVs) in which the donor star is still on (or close to) the Zero Age Main Sequence (ZAMS) at the onset of mass transfer to the white dwarf. Roche lobe geometry and angular momentum dissipation play an integral part in affecting the stability of the CV''s evolution. The CV is said to be dynamically unstable when the rate of mass transfer from the donor to the accretor increases precipitously until it exceeds the Eddington Limit. At this point, the accretion luminosity becomes greater than the Eddington luminosity and the accretor (white dwarf) cannot accrete further mass. At this point the two stars share a common envelope and most likely combine into one larger mass (this is known as a merger). We comprehensively delineate the initial conditions (mass of the donor and mass of the accretor) for which binaries are stable and unstable. We also find, for the first time, dynamical runaways which occur long after the initial phase of mass transfer <img src="/content/thesis/equation.png" />. We label this behavior as a "Latent Dynamical Instability" (LDI). The conditions for which LDIs occur have also been mapped out and are shown to be strongly correlated with the internal structure of the donor star.</p>\r\n<h4><a href="/content/thesis/Honours_Thesis.pdf">Full Thesis </a><span class="linkgreen" style="font-weight:normal;font-size:14px;font-style:italic;">(22MB pdf)</span> </h4>\r\n</div> '),
(13, 'projects', 'Programming', 1, '<div class="programming">\r\n<h4>Web Design</h4>\r\n<p>Currently Web Design is one of my more refined skill. In the past year I have worked on a total of 4 websites; the <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/old">old version</a> of jacobhooey.com, <a href="http://www.pompouspanda.com">pompouspanda.com</a>, the current version of jacobhooey.com (built from scratch) and my current project <a href="http://www.brokenportuguese.com/">brokenportuguese.com</a>. I have a detailed article about the changes made jacobhooey.com and you can access it <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=home#2">here</a>. Most of these sites used either wordpress or joomla (with major coding overhauls) but I am proud to say that the current version of jacobhooey.com was written all by myself. There are a couple of plugins that I integrated to improve the aesthetics, but overall the style and php database access was entirely my doing. As I work on <a href="http://www.brokenportuguese.com/">brokenportuguese.com</a> I continue to refine my skills and hope to continue designing websites for a very long time.</p> \r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>JavaScript</h4>\r\n<p>I am currently in the process of learning JavaScript and I am making great progress through a site called <a href="http://www.codecademy.com/">codeacademy.com</a>. Currently I have learned to write a game of rock, paper, scissors and I am working on learning how to code a simple game of Blackjack.</p>\r\n<p>My goal is to eventually use JavaScript in conjunction with <a href="http://unity3d.com/">Unity3d</a> to develop an awesome side-scrolling, platform video game.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>C++</h4>\r\n<p>My knowledge of C++ is basic but ever expanding. Currently I have developed a simple text based game of "Higher and Lower". If you wish to try it out click the <strong>Developed Video Games</strong> tab at the top of this page.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>JAVA Development</h4>\r\n<p>I have quite a bit of training in java, although I haven''t used it in a couple years. I took two course at <a href="http://www.ubishops.ca/index.html">Bishop''s University</a> (CSC111 - Programming Methodology and CSC121 - Advanced Programming Techniques) both of which specialized in coding with JAVA using the Netbeans IDE. </p>\r\n<p>The first time I used JAVA professionally was when I worked for <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#3">TASKE Technologies</a> as a Quality Assurance Specialist. In this position I had to find and test bugs in their software which was written using JAVA and glassfish.\r\n</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>Bishop''s University</h4>\r\n<p>Bishop''s University was the first opportunity I had to apply my programming skills in a professional setting. As a <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#5">Undergraduate Student Research Assistant</a> I used <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis#3">FORTRAN and IDL</a> to organize and analysis data. A more detailed explanation of how this was developed can be found here. Eventually I used this developed software to speed up data analysis for my <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis#1">Honours Thesis</a>.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>The Beginning</h4>\r\n<p>I have always been interested in programming, even at a very young age. I remember the first website I ever created; I was in 7th grade and my dad had brought home our first computer. Shortly after browsing and exploring the web I put it upon myself to start creating my own webpage.I was crude, with a solid colour background, an assortment of images I pulled from the web, and a giant beer advertisement at the top (because I used free web hosting, they got to decide the ads). Ever since then I have had a desire to understand how computers work and have always tried to find the most efficient way to get things done.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>'),
(14, 'contact', 'General Inquiries', 1, '<h4>General Inquiries</h4>\r\n<p>for questions regarding the overall site design and layout, or if you have comments or suggestions on how to improve the site, send an email to: <a href="mailto:support@pompouspanda.com">support@pompouspanda.com</a>\r\n</p> '),
(15, 'home', 'Home', 1, '<a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#5">\r\n<img src="http://www.jacobhooey.com/content/homepage/medal.jpg" class="homepageImage" style="padding:30px 0 0 0;"></a>\r\n<div class="homepage">\r\n<p>Recipient of the <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#5">Queen Elizabeth Diamond Jubilee Medal</a> for service excellence in the Federal Government. (left)</p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=projects">Programming languages</a> I have worked with include  CSS, HTML, mySQL and PHP for the development of this website and  used WordPress to create this websites <a href="/old/">beta version</a> and <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=projects#3">brokenportuguese.com</a>. I have also used C#, JAVA, <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis#3">FORTRAN</a>, C++, <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis#3">IDL</a>, Javascript, MIPS assembly for various projects throughout the years.</p>\r\n<p>Gained extensive training in the use of Oracle Peoplesoft 8.9, an HR management tool, while working for  <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#3">Shared Services Canada</a> while working on the PeopleSoft service desk team</p>\r\n<p>Provided Quality Assurance for <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#3">Taske Technology</a> (a java software developer), and for <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=resume#3">Health Canada</a> during their migration to PeopleSoft.</p>\r\n<p >Graduated from Bishop''s University with a Bachelors of Science Honours degree in <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis">Physics and Mathematics</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Studied <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=projects#2">Architecture</a> for a short period at McGill University</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=thesis">\r\n<img src="http://www.jacobhooey.com/content/homepage/Dynamical-Instabilities.jpg" class="homepageImage" ></a>\r\n<a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=projects#2"><img src="/content/homepage/Presentation2.JPG" class="homepageImage"></a>\r\n<a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=artwork"><img src="/content/homepage/Bird-Composition.JPG" class="homepageImage" ></a>\r\n'),
(16, 'home', 'The making of Jacobhooey.com', 2, '        <h4>The Beginning</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/history/old-site.jpg" rel="shadowbox[history]" title="The Old Site" >\r\n<img src="/content/history/old-site.jpg" class = "imgRight"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<p>It all started with WordPress. It had been a couple years since I had done any Web Design and so when I set up my hosting with BlueHost, and saw their simple script option for installing WordPress, I jumped at the chance to have my framework constructed for me. After fiddling with all the features and exploring what all the plugins had to offer I set off and explored the vast array of themes. Finally I settled on a theme called <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/wordpress-theme-dailypress/">Daily Press</a>. From there I set out to complete the monumental task of customizing the theme to suit my particular needs. I changed the colour scheme, edited all the images, created a logo and customized the sidebar using php and html. If you want to navigate the old site here is the link: <a href="/old/">jacobhooey.com/old/</a></p>\r\n<h4>Content Creation</h4>\r\n<p>At this point I started introducing content, writing articles, uploading photos, creating pages and customizing the pages to display certain categories (this was challenging because I couldn''t find a plugin so I had to code these page templates by hand). I also dabbled in JavaScript to create <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/old/resume">expandable content</a> to make my resume more accessible. After I created all the content I wished to display my skills in french, so I installed the plugin <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/qtranslate/">qtranslate</a>, and then translated almost all of the content on the site.</p>\r\n<h4>The Turning Point</h4>\r\n<p>At this point I realized I had strayed from my original intention for the website, which was to create a showcase of my abilities that would enhance a prospective employers experience of my resume. I had essentially create a blog with an excess of content and so I realized I needed to escape the WordPress framework or my site might always evolve back into a blog. And so began my journey of pushing the limits of my HTML and CSS knowledge as well as a learning from the ground up PHP and mySQL.</p>\r\n<a href="/content/history/WebsiteLayout.jpg" rel="shadowbox[history]" title="Design Image" >\r\n<img src="/content/history/WebsiteLayout.jpg" class = "imgLeft" />\r\n</a>\r\n<h4>New Site Design</h4>\r\n<p>This time I was determined to have a plan and to no longer explore blindly. So I fired up the old <a href="http://www.gimp.org/">GIMP image editor</a> and created a template for my new site. Then I started to collect my tools. The first was to find a nice plugin that could create the tabbed navigation I wanted. After analyzing and debating all the choices I settled on <a href="http://www.ndoherty.biz/tag/coda-slider/">Coda Slider</a> for its simplicity and the ability to customize. With this new plan and slider plugin I went about creating the index.html page and the style.css. </p>\r\n<h4>Dividing the Site Into Sections</h4>\r\n<p>I divided the site into 5 sections: Logo, Main nav, content/CodaSlider, social networking buttons and Footer. For the logo I designed it so that it wasn''t an image making it easily customizable. The main navigation was tricky, creating the "tree" layout, but with a little css margin magic I managed to make it look pretty darn good. The Coda Slider took a lot of modification, the css that was provided is no longer recognizable, but the JavaScript was left intact. The tricky part was actually the green border at the top and sometimes it still doesn''t line up with the border on the Social Network div. The social network div was added to provide people a way to like my page and I try to keep it within the realm of networks that I use. and of course I put in a nice footer that allows people to connect to my network profiles.</p>\r\n<h4>Creating a CMS</h4>\r\n<p>Once the layout was created a Content Management System (CMS) needed to be established to easily add and edit content. Luckily I found an article called <a href="http://www.elated.com/articles/cms-in-an-afternoon-php-mysql/">"Build a CMS in an Afternoon with PHP and MySQL" by Matt Doyle</a>, which gave me a great starting point. The only issue was to customize it for my needs. This is where I learned a great deal about php, mySQL and the integration between the two languages. And after a lot of hard work, I am now writing this article in a very user friendly CMS. (note: I am currently using the style.css provided by Matt Doyle, but I have plans to change it when I can find the time)</p>\r\n<a href="/content/history/cms-list-article.jpg" rel="shadowbox[history]" title="List Articles" >\r\n<img src="/content/history/cms-list-article.jpg" class="imgLeft" style = "padding-left:30px;" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href="/content/history/cms-edit-article.jpg" rel="shadowbox[history]" title="Edit Article" >\r\n<img src="/content/history/cms-edit-article.jpg" class="imgRight" style = "padding-top:20px;padding-right:30px;" />\r\n</a>\r\n<h4 style="clear:both;">The Future</h4>\r\n<p>As you can see the site has come together fabulously and runs smoothly in most browsers. I am still working out the kinks in internet explorer and I expect that to be an ongoing project. Overall I am happy with the results and I feel great for having done created this from the ground up. It has given me much more control over my site and there is no longer any magic happening in the background that I don''t control. I hope you enjoy exploring the site and if you have any questions or comments (or job offers :) feel free to email me at <a href="mailto:info@jacobhooey.com">info@jacobhooey.com</a></p>    \r\n'),
(17, 'contact', 'Contact Info', 2, '        <h4>Contact Info</h4>\r\n<p>if you wish to contact me, whether its to offer me a job or to share info about yourself, you can send me an emait to: <a href="mailto:jhooey@gmail.com">jhooey@gmail.com</a> </p>\r\n<p>If you are a member of these popular social networking sites I''ve heard so much about you can click the links in the footer to access my profile pages, or click the links below:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="http://ca.linkedin.com/pub/jacob-hooey/36/130/a48">LinkedIn</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="https://github.com/jhooey">GitHub</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href="http://facebook.com/jhooey">Facebook</a></li>\r\n       <li> <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/jacobhooey">Twitter</a></li>\r\n<li> <a href=" http://pinterest.com/pompouspanda">Pinterest</a></li>\r\n</ul>      '),
(18, 'thesis', 'Presentations', 2, '<div class="center">\r\n<h3>On the Nature of Dynamical Instabilities</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nPhysics Department<br />\r\nBishop&#1267; University\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThursday, May 21, 2009 1:00 pm\r\n</p>\r\n<p class="justify">\r\nThis presentation will explore the theory behind Binary Star Systems (Cataclysmic Variables) and the assumptions under which we are studying these systems. Also it will reveal the results from my calculations obtained using the methods described below.\r\n</p>\r\n<p class="justify">\r\nThrough numerical simulations based on stellar theory and using supercomputers, we are able to theorize about the way binary star systems interact and evolve. For certain initial conditions, the resulting evolutionary tracks are stable. However, given an alternate set of initial conditions, the resulting evolutionary tracks may be highly erratic and unstable. \r\n</p>\r\n<a href="/content/thesis/On-the-Nature-of-Dynamical-Instabilities-(by-Jacob-Hooey).pdf" ><img src="/content/thesis/Dynamical-Instabilities.jpg" style="width:70%;"><br>Download the entire presentation </a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Mass Transfer in Binary Star Systems</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nPhysics Department<br />\r\nBishop&#1267; University\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFriday, February 13, 2009 12:00 pm\r\n</p>\r\n<p class="justify">\r\nThrough numerical simulations based on stellar theory and using supercomputers, we are able to theorize about the way binary star systems interact and evolve. For certain initial conditions, the resulting evolutionary tracks are stable. However, given an alternate set of initial conditions, the resulting evolutionary tracks may be highly erratic and unstable. This presentation will explore the theory behind Binary Star Systems (Cataclysmic Variables) and the assumptions under which we are studying these systems.\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="/content/thesis/Mass-Transfer-in-Binary-Star-Systems-(by-Jacob-Hooey).pdf" >\r\n<img src="/content/thesis/Mass-Transfer.jpg" style="width:70%;"><br>Download the entire presentation </a>\r\n</div>'),
(19, 'thesis', 'FORTRAN and IDL', 3, '        <h4>Analyzing the Data from Simulated Evolutions of Binary Star Systems</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/thesis/IDL/M075J180.JPG" rel="shadowbox[IDL]" title="IDL Graph 1" >\r\n<img src="/content/thesis/IDL/M075J180.JPG" class="imgLeft" style = "padding-top:0px" />\r\n</a>\r\n<p >\r\nWhile working on my thesis I used software that had been previously developed by preceding physicists. This software used the Henyey Method to calculate <strong>the evolution of binary star systems</strong> given certain starting conditions. This software output the results in a single text file that was named using the starting conditions. The software I developed took the output data file and used the file name to <strong>organize it into sub-folders</strong> so that it could be easily found manually. The second function of my software took the output data and wrote an IDL file that would graph certain coordinates depending on our needs. <strong>Then in one step the IDL file could be compiled and 8 graphs were automatically generated with the newest data</strong>.  \r\n</p>\r\n<a href="/content/thesis/IDL/M030J040.JPG" rel="shadowbox[IDL]" title="IDL Graph 2" >\r\n<img src="/content/thesis/IDL/M030J040.JPG" style = "width:40%;float:right; padding: 10px 0 15px 20px;clear:left;" />\r\n</a>\r\n<p>Both of these functions <strong>saved hundreds of man hours</strong>, because the data used to be organized manually and the data used to be copied and pasted into SigmaPlot so a graph could be created manually. This doesn''t sound like a lot of time saved until you realize that for every data set 4-8 graphs needed to be created, and to get accurate results over 100 data sets need to be created (and some needed to be recreated). Therefore my software made it <strong>so that the 800 graphs</strong> that needed to be created in that summer alone, <strong>only 10 needed to be created manually</strong>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately I cannot provide sample code because it is the property of Bishop''s University per the requirements of my contract. But as you can see, I have provided a couple images of the graphs that my code created.\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote style="font-size:14px; font-style:italic"><strong>Note:</strong> When the accretion rate becomes greater than the Eddington Limit, the White Dwarf can no longer accrete all of the mass. This additional mass then beginsto form a common envelope around the binary stars. This leads to a merger of the two stars and (simplified version) this means that the System collapses and is no longer considered a Cataclysmic Variable.</blockquote>\r\n<a href="/content/thesis/IDL/M055J140.JPG" rel="shadowbox[IDL]" title="IDL Graph 3" >\r\n<img src="/content/thesis/IDL/M055J140.JPG" style = "width:50%; margin:auto; padding: 20px 0 20px 0;float:left;" />\r\n</a> '),
(20, 'artwork', 'Portfolios', 2, '<div class="containerLeft">\r\n<div class="artbox" style="width:80%;">\r\n<h4>McGill Entrance Portfolio</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio(jacob-hooey).pdf" title="McGill Entrance Portfolio">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_1.jpg" style="width:100%" /><br /> \r\n<span style="float:right;font-size:11px;">dowload portfolio (pdf)</span></a><br />\r\n<p>This portfolio was created from artwork that was completed while at Bishops University and a couple pieces of my earlier work. I used this collection of artwork to gain admittance in the McGill University Architecture program. The most difficult and interesting piece of art in this portfolio was the Hologram, which was developed in my Physics Lab class and took almost a semester to complete. This portfolio contains some of my best work and I plan on continuing to use it to showcase my artistic talent.  </p>\r\n<h4>Samples:</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_2.jpg" rel="shadowbox[entrance]" title="Creating a Hologram">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/thumbs/thumb_McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_2.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_3.jpg" rel="shadowbox[entrance]" title="Soft Stone Sculpture created using a Negative Clay Mold">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/thumbs/thumb_McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_3.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_4.jpg" rel="shadowbox[entrance]" title="Plaster Sculpture">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/thumbs/thumb_McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_4.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_5.jpg" rel="shadowbox[entrance]" title="Photography - Bike Path">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/thumbs/thumb_McGill-Entrance-Portfolio_5.jpg" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="containerRight">\r\n<div class="artbox" style="width:80%;" >\r\n<h4>McGill Architecture Studio Portfolio</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/McGill-Studio-Portfolio-2009(jacob-hooey).pdf" title="McGill Architecture Studio Portfolio">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/McGill-Studio-Portfolio-2009.jpg" style="width:100%" /><br /> \r\n<span style="float:right;font-size:11px;">dowload portfolio (pdf)</span></a><br />\r\n<p>This is a collection of the work I produced in my studio class in Architecture. It contains the final artwork for the two major projects:<br /> <br />\r\n<strong>The Wind-Up Bird Chronicle:</strong> <br / >\r\n<blockquote>This project required me to read an exert from the book "The Wind-up Bird Chronicle" and interpret it artistically. You can see the results of that interpretation inside this protfolio</blockquote>\r\n<strong>The Aviary Project:</strong> <br />\r\n<blockquote>At the beginning of this project I drew a bird that was a combination of three birds. The object of this project was to create a bird sanctuary for my unique bird, and multiple methods were used to represent this idea. </blockquote>\r\n </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="containerLeft">\r\n<div class="artbox"  style="width:80%;">\r\n<h4>Personal Portfolio</h4>\r\n<a href="/content/portfolios/Personal-Portfolio(jacob-hooey).pdf" title="Personal Portfolio">\r\n<img src="/content/portfolios/Personal-Portfolio.jpg" style="width:100%" /><br /> \r\n<span style="float:right;font-size:11px;">dowload portfolio (pdf)</span></a><br />\r\n<p>This portfolio was a personal project. I wanted to collected all my best work and present it in a comprehensive format. Most of this work is from my Freehand Drawing class and my Architecture Studio class. The individual works of art can be found in the artwork section of this website.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>'),
(21, 'projects', 'Developed Video Games', 2, '<h3>Higher or Lower</h3>\r\n<h4>What is it?</h4>\r\n<p>Higher and Lower is my first c++ program. It is a simple command prompt application that draws a card for you so that you will have to guess whether the next one will be higher or lower.</p>\r\n<img src="/games/HL-preview.JPG">\r\n<h4>What''s Next?</h4>\r\n<p>I currently classify this as my alpha release because I hope to add functionality to have multiple players, who can compete against each other. And I eventually want to create a pretty graphical interface.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I try it out?</h4>\r\n<p>Glad you asked. You can download from the link below:</p>\r\n<p>Release (Alpha): <a href="/games/Higher or Lower - Alpha Release.zip" target="_blank" title="Higher or Lower?">Higher_or_Lower.zip</a></p>\r\n<h4>How did you do it?</h4>\r\n<p>I have posted all my source code online using github.com and my project was created in <a href="http://www.netbeans.org/" target="_blank" title="Netbeans IDE">Netbeans 7.0.1</a></p>\r\n<p>Source Code: <a href="https://github.com/jhooey/HigherLower-cardgame" title="Check it out!">Check it Out</a></p>'),
(22, 'projects', 'Architecture', 3, '<h3>The Aviary and The Birdcage</h3>\r\n<div class="containerLeft" style="padding-bottom:40px;">\r\n<div class="artbox">\r\n<h4>The Aviary</h4>\r\n<p> The aviary then transferred the birdcage idea to a physical topography at a very large scale.\r\nThe pavilion found within the aviary was made to look like an extension of the hillside creating\r\na familiar habitat for this merged bird. The merged bird can then interact with the other\r\nbirds in the aviary on the cantilevered section of the pavilion. People who wish to view the\r\nbirds must travel up the stairs surrounded by waterfalls to reach this cantilevered section.\r\n</p>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/Presentation1.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Presentation 1">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/Presentation1.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/Presentation2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Presentation 2">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/Presentation2.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-full-poster.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Poster">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-full-poster.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-pavilion.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Pavilion">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-pavilion.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-pavilion-floor-plan.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Pavilion Floor Plan">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-pavilion-floor-plan.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-pavilion-section.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Pavilion Section">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-pavilion-section.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-pavilion-side-elevation.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Pavilion Side Elevation">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-pavilion-side-elevation.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric1.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Perspective and Axonometric 1">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric1.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Perspective and Axonometric 2">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric2.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric3.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Perspective and Axonometric 3">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-perspective-and-axonometric3.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-perspectives1.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Perspectives 1">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-perspectives1.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-perspectives2.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Perspectives 2">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-perspectives2.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-site-plan.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Site Plan">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-site-plan.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-territorial-section.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Territorial Section">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-territorial-section.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-Elevation-Sketch.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Elevation Sketch">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-Elevation-Sketch.JPG" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/aviary/aviary-Section-Sketch.JPG" rel="shadowbox[aviary]" title="Aviary Section Sketch">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/aviary/thumbs/aviary-Section-Sketch.JPG" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="containerRight">\r\n<div class="artbox">\r\n\r\n<h4>The Bird Cage</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nThe birdcage represents the internal structure of a merger between three birds. The use of rib cages represents the idea of a cage found within a bird that anchors it in its physical form. This is the 3rd project in a series of 4 which all began with <a href="http://www.jacobhooey.com/index.php?action=artwork#1">bird drawings</a>. The birdcage is bent steel wire soldered together to create rib cage like structures.\r\n</p>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/birdcage/birdcage1.jpg" rel="shadowbox[birdcage]" title="Birdcage Sculpture - Photo 1">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/birdcage/thumbs/birdcage1.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/birdcage/birdcage2.jpg" rel="shadowbox[birdcage]" title="Birdcage Sculpture - Photo 2">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/birdcage/thumbs/birdcage2.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/birdcage/birdcage3.jpg" rel="shadowbox[birdcage]" title="Birdcage Sculpture - Photo 1">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/birdcage/thumbs/birdcage3.jpg" /></a>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/birdcage/birdcage-side-elevation.jpg" rel="shadowbox[birdcage]" title="Birdcage Side Elevation">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/birdcage/thumbs/birdcage-side-elevation.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="center" style="clear:both;">\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>An Essay about the History,  Engineering and Collapse of the World Trade Center</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">\r\nThis essay was a collaborative research paper regarding the history, collapse and future of the World Trade Center. This Essay looks at the structural significance of the two towers and how the construction methods contributed to their eventual collapse. We decided to present our essay digitally through the structure of a website. In this way we were able to isolate the important subjects and present them separately, while keeping the overall structure of the essay intact. Also this format provided us with the unique opportunity to incorporate links to videos, which would normally be omitted from a standard pen and paper essay. If you wish to see the final product feel free to follow this link:</p>\r\n<p >\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/Essay/introduction.html">The World Trade Center<br />\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/Essay/wtc-preview.jpg" width="70%">\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class="justify">\r\nAlthough this was a collaboration the task of programming the website was left completely up to me. We all decided on a free css layout and I modified the structure and code to suit our needs. Although this was not my first website, it definitely was a very good learning experience and I used it to expand my knowledge of css even further.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>A Poster Paper about the Pyramid of the Moon</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="/content/architecture/Poster-Paper.jpg"  title="A Poster Paper about the Pyramid of the Moon">\r\n<img src="/content/architecture/Poster-Paper.jpg" style="width:40%;"/></a>\r\n\r\n</div>'),
(23, 'projects', 'BrokenPortuguese.com', 4, '        <h3>The designing of <a href="http://www.brokenportuguese.com">BrokenPortuguese.com</a></h3>\r\n<p>BrokenPortuguese.com came into being when one of my family members requested their own website. She had the idea of making a blog related to her cooking and how it relates to her Portuguese background. We start by setting her up with some web hosting through bluehost.com and choosing to use Wordpress for its ease of use.</p>\r\n<p>Currently the project is under development and we are hoping to have it fully operational in the near future</p>      ');

